<h3>How do you not know who's posting what even if their username is displayed?</h3>

<p>
  Once a user is in the site they can invite other people. Once that starts happening, we stop
  knowing who's who because sudo !! doesn't store emails. The username (or in old-school hacker
  terms, and what we refer to it as, the handle) is the only identifier that the site is made
  aware of on purpose, and that alone isn't enough to pinpoint who's saying what.
</p>

